Exemplo Log√≠stica

Lucca Pavan

08/04/2021

`Carga` <- sample(seq(500,1000,10), 100, replace = TRUE) # em mil kilos
`Tempo no cliente` <-  0.15 * `Carga` + rnorm(100, 30,30) # em minutos

Dados <- tibble(`Tempo no cliente`, `Carga`)

head(Dados)
## # A tibble: 6 x 2
##   `Tempo no cliente` Carga
##                <dbl> <dbl>
## 1               190.   650
## 2               127.   810
## 3               136.   660
## 4               209.  1000
## 5               141.   730
## 6               129.   620
regressao <- lm(`Tempo no cliente` ~ Carga, Dados)

summary(regressao)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = `Tempo no cliente` ~ Carga, data = Dados)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -68.065 -17.578  -2.634  15.335  59.769 
## 
## Coefficients:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept) 46.94277   15.44788   3.039  0.00305 ** 
## Carga        0.12888    0.01991   6.473 3.82e-09 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 26.57 on 98 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.2995, Adjusted R-squared:  0.2924 
## F-statistic:  41.9 on 1 and 98 DF,  p-value: 3.823e-09
ggplot(Dados, aes(`Carga`, `Tempo no cliente`))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method='lm')
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Dados$chuva <- Dados$`Tempo no cliente` > 150
write.csv(Dados, "Dados.csv")
head(Dados)
## # A tibble: 6 x 3
##   `Tempo no cliente` Carga chuva
##                <dbl> <dbl> <lgl>
## 1               190.   650 TRUE 
## 2               127.   810 FALSE
## 3               136.   660 FALSE
## 4               209.  1000 TRUE 
## 5               141.   730 FALSE
## 6               129.   620 FALSE
regressao2 <- lm(`Tempo no cliente` ~ Carga + chuva, Dados)

summary(regressao2)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = `Tempo no cliente` ~ Carga + chuva, data = Dados)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -51.626 -11.823   2.433  12.392  36.335 
## 
## Coefficients:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept) 80.39043   10.77475   7.461 3.68e-11 ***
## Carga        0.06053    0.01470   4.119 8.02e-05 ***
## chuvaTRUE   43.71293    3.96155  11.034  < 2e-16 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 17.79 on 97 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.6894, Adjusted R-squared:  0.683 
## F-statistic: 107.6 on 2 and 97 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16
ggplot(Dados, aes(`Carga`, `Tempo no cliente`, colour = chuva))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method='lm')
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

ggplot(Dados, aes(`Carga`, `Tempo no cliente`))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method='lm')+
    facet_wrap(~chuva)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
